### Execution Explanation

The DSL program defines a `SmartRoom` system. When run, each macro builds metamodel structs:

1. `system "SmartRoom" do ... end` — creates an `IoTSystem` struct, evaluates the block, returns the populated struct.

2. Inside the block, `node`, `topic`, `broker` calls add structs to the system.

3. `sensor :temp_sensor do ... end` — sets a Context Variable pointing to a new `Sensor` struct. The `trigger` and `publish` calls inside the block add `Trigger`, `SimpleCondition`, and `PublishAction` structs to that sensor. When the `end` is reached, the sensor is finalized and added to the system.

4. `actuator :cooling_fan do ... end` — similarly builds an `Actuator` with `ActuatorAction` entries, one per `on_message` call.

5. `coordinator :room_safety do ... end` — builds a `Coordinator` with a `Rule` containing a `CompoundCondition` (AND of two topic checks).

The `Printer` then traverses this struct tree and displays every component, proving the metamodel was correctly instantiated. The Data Flow section computes the message routing by matching sensor publish topics to actuator/coordinator subscriptions.

### DSL Syntax to Metamodel Mapping

| DSL Keyword          | Metamodel Class              | Fowler Pattern            |
| -------------------- | ---------------------------- | ------------------------- |
| `system ... do`      | IoTSystem                    | Nested Closure (Ch.38)    |
| `broker`             | IoTSystem attributes         | Function Sequence (Ch.33) |
| `node`               | Node                         | Function Sequence         |
| `topic`              | Topic                        | Function Sequence         |
| `sensor ... do`      | Sensor                       | Nested Closure            |
| `trigger ... do`     | Trigger                      | Nested Closure (nested)   |
| `condition`          | SimpleCondition + Expression | Function Sequence         |
| `compound_condition` | CompoundCondition            | Function Sequence         |
| `publish`            | PublishAction                | Function Sequence         |
| `actuator ... do`    | Actuator                     | Nested Closure            |
| `on_message`         | ActuatorAction               | Function Sequence         |
| `coordinator ... do` | Coordinator                  | Nested Closure            |
| `rule ... do`        | Rule                         | Nested Closure (nested)   |

<!-- livebook:{"break_markdown":true} -->

### Metamodel

```elixir
# =============================================================================
# IoT DSL Metamodel
# =============================================================================
# Each struct below maps 1:1 to a class in the metamodel class diagram.
# Enumerations are represented as atoms (e.g., :temperature, :at_least_once).
# Abstract classes (Condition, Action, Expression) are represented by their
# concrete subtypes — Elixir uses tagged tuples/structs for polymorphism.
# =============================================================================

defmodule IoTDSL.Metamodel do

  # --- Root Container ---
  defmodule IoTSystem do
    @moduledoc "Root of the metamodel. Contains all nodes, topics, sensors, actuators, coordinators."
    defstruct name: "",
              broker_host: "localhost",
              broker_port: 1883,
              nodes: [],         # [Node]
              topics: [],        # [Topic]
              sensors: [],       # [Sensor]
              actuators: [],     # [Actuator]
              coordinators: []   # [Coordinator]
  end

  # --- Structural Elements ---
  defmodule Node do
    @moduledoc "A physical Raspberry Pi device."
    defstruct name: nil,         # atom, e.g. :pi4
              ip_address: ""     # String
  end

  defmodule Topic do
    @moduledoc "An MQTT communication channel."
    # QoS enum: :at_most_once | :at_least_once | :exactly_once
    defstruct name: "",          # String, e.g. "temperature/high"
              qos: :at_most_once # QoS
  end

  # --- Sensors ---
  defmodule Sensor do
    @moduledoc "A data input device that reads from GPIO and publishes to topics."
    # SensorType enum: :temperature | :humidity | :motion | :light | :distance
    defstruct name: nil,          # atom
              type: nil,          # SensorType
              gpio_pin: nil,      # Integer
              sample_rate: nil,   # {Integer, :seconds | :minutes | :milliseconds}
              deployed_on: nil,   # atom (node name)
              publishes_to: [],   # [String] (topic names)
              triggers: []        # [Trigger]
  end

  defmodule Trigger do
    @moduledoc "A sensor-local reactive behavior: condition + actions."
    defstruct name: nil,          # atom
              condition: nil,     # Condition (SimpleCondition | TemporalCondition | CompoundCondition)
              actions: []         # [Action] (PublishAction | ActivateAction)
  end

  # --- Actuators ---
  defmodule Actuator do
    @moduledoc "A controllable output device on GPIO."
    # ActuatorType enum: :relay | :led | :buzzer | :servo
    defstruct name: nil,          # atom
              type: nil,          # ActuatorType
              gpio_pin: nil,      # Integer
              deployed_on: nil,   # atom (node name)
              subscribes_to: [],  # [String] (topic names)
              actions: []         # [ActuatorAction]
  end

  defmodule ActuatorAction do
    @moduledoc "Maps an incoming topic to a physical response."
    # State enum: :on | :off
    defstruct from_topic: "",     # String (topic name)
              state: :on,         # State
              duration: nil       # {Integer, :seconds | ...} or nil (permanent)
  end

  # --- Coordinator ---
  defmodule Coordinator do
    @moduledoc "Cross-sensor logic component that subscribes to multiple topics."
    defstruct name: nil,          # atom
              deployed_on: nil,   # atom (node name)
              subscribes_to: [],  # [String] (topic names)
              publishes_to: [],   # [String] (topic names derived from rules)
              rules: []           # [Rule]
  end

  defmodule Rule do
    @moduledoc "A coordinator rule: compound condition + actions."
    defstruct name: nil,          # atom
              condition: nil,     # Condition
              actions: []         # [Action]
  end

  # --- Conditions (abstract hierarchy) ---
  # Condition <|-- SimpleCondition | TemporalCondition | CompoundCondition

  defmodule SimpleCondition do
    @moduledoc "Compares two expressions with an operator."
    # Operator enum: :greater_than | :less_than | :equals
    defstruct operator: nil,      # Operator
              left: nil,          # Expression (Literal | SensorValue)
              right: nil          # Expression (Literal | SensorValue)
  end

  defmodule TemporalCondition do
    @moduledoc "Wraps a base condition with a time requirement."
    defstruct base_condition: nil, # Condition
              duration: nil        # {Integer, :seconds | ...}
  end

  defmodule CompoundCondition do
    @moduledoc "Combines 2+ conditions with AND/OR."
    # LogicalOperator enum: :and | :or
    defstruct logical_operator: :and,  # LogicalOperator
              conditions: []           # [Condition], min 2
  end

  # --- Actions (abstract hierarchy) ---
  # Action <|-- PublishAction | ActivateAction

  defmodule PublishAction do
    @moduledoc "Publishes a message to an MQTT topic."
    defstruct topic: "",          # String (topic name)
              message: ""         # String
  end

  defmodule ActivateAction do
    @moduledoc "Directly activates an actuator."
    defstruct actuator: nil,      # atom (actuator name)
              duration: nil       # {Integer, :seconds | ...} or nil
  end

  # --- Expressions (abstract hierarchy) ---
  # Expression <|-- Literal | SensorValue

  defmodule Literal do
    @moduledoc "A fixed value: number, boolean, or string."
    defstruct value: nil          # any
  end

  defmodule SensorValue do
    @moduledoc "A dynamic runtime value from the sensor reading."
    defstruct field: "value"      # String, e.g. "value", "timestamp"
  end
end
```

### DSL

```elixir
# =============================================================================
# IoT Internal DSL — Expression Builder
# =============================================================================
# Technique: Nested Closure (Fowler Ch.38) + Object Scoping (Fowler Ch.36)
#
# In Elixir, macros with `do` blocks implement the Nested Closure pattern:
#   - The `do` block is the closure
#   - The macro evaluates it within a controlled context
#   - Agent (process) stores the Context Variables (Fowler Ch.35 §175)
#
# The DSL user writes natural-looking code. Behind the scenes, each macro
# call builds metamodel structs and accumulates them into the IoTSystem.
# =============================================================================

defmodule IoTDSL do
  alias IoTDSL.Metamodel.{
    IoTSystem, Node, Topic, Sensor, Actuator, ActuatorAction,
    Coordinator, Rule, Trigger,
    SimpleCondition, TemporalCondition, CompoundCondition,
    PublishAction, ActivateAction, Literal, SensorValue
  }

  # ── Context Variable Storage ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  # We use the process dictionary as our Context Variable (Fowler §175).
  # This tracks what we're currently building (which sensor, actuator, etc.)

  defp put_ctx(key, value), do: Process.put({:iot_dsl, key}, value)
  defp get_ctx(key), do: Process.get({:iot_dsl, key})
  defp delete_ctx(key), do: Process.delete({:iot_dsl, key})

  # ── Top-level: system ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Fowler Ch.38: The parent function sets up context, evaluates the closure,
  # then tears down and returns the result.

  defmacro system(name, do: block) do
    quote do
      # Initialize the system context
      IoTDSL.init_system(unquote(name))
      # Evaluate the closure (the do block contents)
      unquote(block)
      # Tear down: return the built system
      IoTDSL.finalize_system()
    end
  end

  def init_system(name) do
    put_ctx(:system, %IoTSystem{name: name})
  end

  def finalize_system do
    system = get_ctx(:system)
    delete_ctx(:system)
    # Reverse lists to maintain declaration order
    %{system |
      nodes: Enum.reverse(system.nodes),
      topics: Enum.reverse(system.topics),
      sensors: Enum.reverse(system.sensors),
      actuators: Enum.reverse(system.actuators),
      coordinators: Enum.reverse(system.coordinators)
    }
  end

  # ── Broker ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  defmacro broker(host, opts \\ []) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.set_broker(unquote(host), unquote(opts))
    end
  end

  def set_broker(host, opts) do
    system = get_ctx(:system)
    port = Keyword.get(opts, :port, 1883)
    put_ctx(:system, %{system | broker_host: host, broker_port: port})
  end

  # ── Node ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  defmacro node(name, opts) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.add_node(unquote(name), unquote(opts))
    end
  end

  def add_node(name, opts) do
    system = get_ctx(:system)
    node = %Node{name: name, ip_address: Keyword.get(opts, :ip, "")}
    put_ctx(:system, %{system | nodes: [node | system.nodes]})
  end

  # ── Topic ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  defmacro topic(name, opts \\ []) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.add_topic(unquote(name), unquote(opts))
    end
  end

  def add_topic(name, opts) do
    system = get_ctx(:system)
    topic = %Topic{name: name, qos: Keyword.get(opts, :qos, :at_most_once)}
    put_ctx(:system, %{system | topics: [topic | system.topics]})
  end

  # ── Sensor ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Nested Closure: the sensor macro evaluates its do block, during which
  # trigger/publish calls are captured into the current sensor context.

  defmacro sensor(name, opts \\ [], do: block) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.begin_sensor(unquote(name), unquote(opts))
      unquote(block)
      IoTDSL.end_sensor()
    end
  end

  def begin_sensor(name, opts) do
    sensor = %Sensor{
      name: name,
      type: Keyword.get(opts, :type),
      gpio_pin: Keyword.get(opts, :gpio_pin),
      sample_rate: Keyword.get(opts, :sample_rate),
      deployed_on: Keyword.get(opts, :deployed_on),
      publishes_to: Keyword.get(opts, :publishes_to, [])
    }
    put_ctx(:current_sensor, sensor)
  end

  def end_sensor do
    sensor = get_ctx(:current_sensor)
    sensor = %{sensor | triggers: Enum.reverse(sensor.triggers)}
    delete_ctx(:current_sensor)

    system = get_ctx(:system)
    put_ctx(:system, %{system | sensors: [sensor | system.sensors]})
  end

  # ── Trigger (inside sensor) ──────────────────────────────────────────────

  defmacro trigger(name, do: block) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.begin_trigger(unquote(name))
      unquote(block)
      IoTDSL.end_trigger()
    end
  end

  def begin_trigger(name) do
    put_ctx(:current_trigger, %Trigger{name: name, actions: []})
  end

  def end_trigger do
    trigger = get_ctx(:current_trigger)
    trigger = %{trigger | actions: Enum.reverse(trigger.actions)}
    delete_ctx(:current_trigger)

    sensor = get_ctx(:current_sensor)
    put_ctx(:current_sensor, %{sensor | triggers: [trigger | sensor.triggers]})
  end

  # ── Condition: when ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # `condition :value, :greater_than, 30` → SimpleCondition

  defmacro condition(left, operator, right) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.set_condition(unquote(left), unquote(operator), unquote(right))
    end
  end

  def set_condition(left, operator, right) do
    left_expr = case left do
      :value     -> %SensorValue{field: "value"}
      :timestamp -> %SensorValue{field: "timestamp"}
      other      -> %Literal{value: other}
    end

    right_expr = case right do
      :value     -> %SensorValue{field: "value"}
      :timestamp -> %SensorValue{field: "timestamp"}
      other      -> %Literal{value: other}
    end

    cond_struct = %SimpleCondition{
      operator: operator,
      left: left_expr,
      right: right_expr
    }

    # Set condition on whichever context is active (trigger or rule)
    case get_ctx(:current_trigger) do
      nil ->
        rule = get_ctx(:current_rule)
        put_ctx(:current_rule, %{rule | condition: cond_struct})
      trigger ->
        put_ctx(:current_trigger, %{trigger | condition: cond_struct})
    end
  end

  # ── Compound Condition (for coordinator rules) ───────────────────────────
  # `compound_condition :and, ["temperature/high", "distance/close"]`

  defmacro compound_condition(logical_op, topic_names) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.set_compound_condition(unquote(logical_op), unquote(topic_names))
    end
  end

  def set_compound_condition(logical_op, topic_names) do
    # Each topic name becomes a SimpleCondition checking topic == name
    conditions = Enum.map(topic_names, fn topic_name ->
      %SimpleCondition{
        operator: :equals,
        left: %SensorValue{field: "topic"},
        right: %Literal{value: topic_name}
      }
    end)

    compound = %CompoundCondition{
      logical_operator: logical_op,
      conditions: conditions
    }

    rule = get_ctx(:current_rule)
    put_ctx(:current_rule, %{rule | condition: compound})
  end

  # ── Actions ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  defmacro publish(topic_name, opts \\ []) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.add_publish_action(unquote(topic_name), unquote(opts))
    end
  end

  def add_publish_action(topic_name, opts) do
    action = %PublishAction{
      topic: topic_name,
      message: Keyword.get(opts, :message, "")
    }

    # Add to whichever context is active
    case get_ctx(:current_trigger) do
      nil ->
        rule = get_ctx(:current_rule)
        put_ctx(:current_rule, %{rule | actions: [action | rule.actions]})
      trigger ->
        put_ctx(:current_trigger, %{trigger | actions: [action | trigger.actions]})
    end

    # Also track publish topics for sensors
    case get_ctx(:current_sensor) do
      nil -> :ok
      sensor ->
        unless topic_name in sensor.publishes_to do
          put_ctx(:current_sensor, %{sensor | publishes_to: [topic_name | sensor.publishes_to]})
        end
    end
  end

  defmacro activate(actuator_name, opts \\ []) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.add_activate_action(unquote(actuator_name), unquote(opts))
    end
  end

  def add_activate_action(actuator_name, opts) do
    action = %ActivateAction{
      actuator: actuator_name,
      duration: Keyword.get(opts, :duration)
    }

    case get_ctx(:current_trigger) do
      nil ->
        rule = get_ctx(:current_rule)
        put_ctx(:current_rule, %{rule | actions: [action | rule.actions]})
      trigger ->
        put_ctx(:current_trigger, %{trigger | actions: [action | trigger.actions]})
    end
  end

  # ── Actuator ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  defmacro actuator(name, opts \\ [], do: block) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.begin_actuator(unquote(name), unquote(opts))
      unquote(block)
      IoTDSL.end_actuator()
    end
  end

  def begin_actuator(name, opts) do
    actuator = %Actuator{
      name: name,
      type: Keyword.get(opts, :type),
      gpio_pin: Keyword.get(opts, :gpio_pin),
      deployed_on: Keyword.get(opts, :deployed_on)
    }
    put_ctx(:current_actuator, actuator)
  end

  def end_actuator do
    actuator = get_ctx(:current_actuator)
    topics = actuator.actions |> Enum.map(& &1.from_topic) |> Enum.uniq()
    actuator = %{actuator |
      subscribes_to: topics,
      actions: Enum.reverse(actuator.actions)
    }
    delete_ctx(:current_actuator)

    system = get_ctx(:system)
    put_ctx(:system, %{system | actuators: [actuator | system.actuators]})
  end

  # ── on_message (inside actuator) ─────────────────────────────────────────

  defmacro on_message(topic_name, opts) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.add_actuator_action(unquote(topic_name), unquote(opts))
    end
  end

  def add_actuator_action(topic_name, opts) do
    action = %ActuatorAction{
      from_topic: topic_name,
      state: Keyword.get(opts, :turn, :on),
      duration: Keyword.get(opts, :for)
    }

    actuator = get_ctx(:current_actuator)
    put_ctx(:current_actuator, %{actuator | actions: [action | actuator.actions]})
  end

  # ── Coordinator ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  defmacro coordinator(name, opts \\ [], do: block) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.begin_coordinator(unquote(name), unquote(opts))
      unquote(block)
      IoTDSL.end_coordinator()
    end
  end

  def begin_coordinator(name, opts) do
    coordinator = %Coordinator{
      name: name,
      deployed_on: Keyword.get(opts, :deployed_on),
      subscribes_to: Keyword.get(opts, :subscribes_to, [])
    }
    put_ctx(:current_coordinator, coordinator)
  end

  def end_coordinator do
    coord = get_ctx(:current_coordinator)
    # Collect published topics from rules
    pub_topics = coord.rules
      |> Enum.flat_map(fn r -> Enum.map(r.actions, fn
        %PublishAction{topic: t} -> t
        _ -> nil
      end) end)
      |> Enum.reject(&is_nil/1)
      |> Enum.uniq()

    coord = %{coord |
      publishes_to: pub_topics,
      rules: Enum.reverse(coord.rules)
    }
    delete_ctx(:current_coordinator)

    system = get_ctx(:system)
    put_ctx(:system, %{system | coordinators: [coord | system.coordinators]})
  end

  # ── Rule (inside coordinator) ────────────────────────────────────────────

  defmacro rule(name, do: block) do
    quote do
      IoTDSL.begin_rule(unquote(name))
      unquote(block)
      IoTDSL.end_rule()
    end
  end

  def begin_rule(name) do
    put_ctx(:current_rule, %Rule{name: name, actions: []})
  end

  def end_rule do
    rule = get_ctx(:current_rule)
    rule = %{rule | actions: Enum.reverse(rule.actions)}
    delete_ctx(:current_rule)

    coord = get_ctx(:current_coordinator)
    put_ctx(:current_coordinator, %{coord | rules: [rule | coord.rules]})
  end
end
```

```elixir
# =============================================================================
# IoT DSL Printer — "Execution" of the Metamodel Instance
# =============================================================================
# This module takes a built IoTSystem struct and prints it in a structured way,
# demonstrating that the metamodel was correctly instantiated from the DSL.
# =============================================================================

defmodule IoTDSL.Printer do
  alias IoTDSL.Metamodel.{
    SimpleCondition, CompoundCondition, TemporalCondition,
    PublishAction, ActivateAction, Literal, SensorValue
  }

  def print(%{__struct__: IoTDSL.Metamodel.IoTSystem} = sys) do
    IO.puts("╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗")
    IO.puts("║  IoT System: #{sys.name}")
    IO.puts("║  Broker: #{sys.broker_host}:#{sys.broker_port}")
    IO.puts("╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝")

    IO.puts("\n── Nodes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────")
    Enum.each(sys.nodes, fn node ->
      IO.puts("  📡 #{node.name} (#{node.ip_address})")
    end)

    IO.puts("\n── Topics ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────")
    Enum.each(sys.topics, fn topic ->
      IO.puts("  📨 \"#{topic.name}\" [QoS: #{format_qos(topic.qos)}]")
    end)

    IO.puts("\n── Sensors ────────────────────────────────────────────────────")
    Enum.each(sys.sensors, fn sensor ->
      {rate_val, rate_unit} = sensor.sample_rate
      IO.puts("  🔍 #{sensor.name}")
      IO.puts("     Type: #{sensor.type} | GPIO: #{sensor.gpio_pin} | Rate: #{rate_val} #{rate_unit}")
      IO.puts("     Deployed on: #{sensor.deployed_on}")
      IO.puts("     Publishes to: #{Enum.join(sensor.publishes_to, ", ")}")
      Enum.each(sensor.triggers, fn trigger ->
        IO.puts("     ⚡ Trigger: #{trigger.name}")
        IO.puts("        Condition: #{format_condition(trigger.condition)}")
        Enum.each(trigger.actions, fn action ->
          IO.puts("        Action: #{format_action(action)}")
        end)
      end)
    end)

    IO.puts("\n── Actuators ──────────────────────────────────────────────────")
    Enum.each(sys.actuators, fn actuator ->
      IO.puts("  ⚙️  #{actuator.name}")
      IO.puts("     Type: #{actuator.type} | GPIO: #{actuator.gpio_pin}")
      IO.puts("     Deployed on: #{actuator.deployed_on}")
      IO.puts("     Subscribes to: #{Enum.join(actuator.subscribes_to, ", ")}")
      Enum.each(actuator.actions, fn action ->
        dur = if action.duration, do: " for #{format_duration(action.duration)}", else: ""
        IO.puts("     📩 on \"#{action.from_topic}\" → turn #{action.state |> Atom.to_string() |> String.upcase()}#{dur}")
      end)
    end)

    if length(sys.coordinators) > 0 do
      IO.puts("\n── Coordinators ───────────────────────────────────────────────")
      Enum.each(sys.coordinators, fn coord ->
        IO.puts("  🧠 #{coord.name}")
        IO.puts("     Deployed on: #{coord.deployed_on}")
        IO.puts("     Subscribes to: #{Enum.join(coord.subscribes_to, ", ")}")
        IO.puts("     Publishes to: #{Enum.join(coord.publishes_to, ", ")}")
        Enum.each(coord.rules, fn rule ->
          IO.puts("     📋 Rule: #{rule.name}")
          IO.puts("        Condition: #{format_condition(rule.condition)}")
          Enum.each(rule.actions, fn action ->
            IO.puts("        Action: #{format_action(action)}")
          end)
        end)
      end)
    end

    IO.puts("\n── Data Flow ──────────────────────────────────────────────────")
    Enum.each(sys.sensors, fn sensor ->
      Enum.each(sensor.triggers, fn trigger ->
        Enum.each(trigger.actions, fn
          %PublishAction{topic: topic} ->
            # Find actuators subscribing to this topic
            receivers = sys.actuators
              |> Enum.filter(fn a -> topic in a.subscribes_to end)
              |> Enum.map(fn a -> "#{a.name}" end)
            # Find coordinators subscribing to this topic
            coord_receivers = sys.coordinators
              |> Enum.filter(fn c -> topic in c.subscribes_to end)
              |> Enum.map(fn c -> "#{c.name}" end)
            all = receivers ++ coord_receivers
            if length(all) > 0 do
              IO.puts("  #{sensor.name} ──► \"#{topic}\" ──► #{Enum.join(all, ", ")}")
            end
          _ -> :ok
        end)
      end)
    end)

    # Coordinator flows
    Enum.each(sys.coordinators, fn coord ->
      Enum.each(coord.rules, fn rule ->
        Enum.each(rule.actions, fn
          %PublishAction{topic: topic} ->
            receivers = sys.actuators
              |> Enum.filter(fn a -> topic in a.subscribes_to end)
              |> Enum.map(fn a -> "#{a.name}" end)
            if length(receivers) > 0 do
              IO.puts("  #{coord.name} ──► \"#{topic}\" ──► #{Enum.join(receivers, ", ")}")
            end
          _ -> :ok
        end)
      end)
    end)

    IO.puts("")
    :ok
  end

  # ── Formatting Helpers ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

  defp format_condition(%SimpleCondition{operator: op, left: l, right: r}) do
    "#{format_expr(l)} #{format_operator(op)} #{format_expr(r)}"
  end
  defp format_condition(%CompoundCondition{logical_operator: op, conditions: conds}) do
    op_str = op |> Atom.to_string() |> String.upcase()
    conds |> Enum.map(&format_condition/1) |> Enum.join(" #{op_str} ")
  end
  defp format_condition(%TemporalCondition{base_condition: base, duration: dur}) do
    "#{format_condition(base)} for #{format_duration(dur)}"
  end
  defp format_condition(nil), do: "(none)"

  defp format_expr(%SensorValue{field: f}), do: f
  defp format_expr(%Literal{value: v}), do: "#{inspect(v)}"

  defp format_operator(:greater_than), do: ">"
  defp format_operator(:less_than), do: "<"
  defp format_operator(:equals), do: "=="

  defp format_action(%PublishAction{topic: t, message: m}) do
    msg = if m != "", do: " (#{m})", else: ""
    "publish → \"#{t}\"#{msg}"
  end
  defp format_action(%ActivateAction{actuator: a, duration: d}) do
    dur = if d, do: " for #{format_duration(d)}", else: ""
    "activate #{a}#{dur}"
  end

  defp format_duration({val, unit}), do: "#{val} #{unit}"
  defp format_duration(nil), do: ""

  defp format_qos(:at_most_once), do: "0 (at most once)"
  defp format_qos(:at_least_once), do: "1 (at least once)"
  defp format_qos(:exactly_once), do: "2 (exactly once)"
end
```

```elixir
# =============================================================================
# IoT DSL Program — Multi-Sensor Safety Alert (Example 3)
# =============================================================================
# This file demonstrates the internal DSL in action.
# A domain expert writes THIS code to define an IoT system.
# The macros build the metamodel structs behind the scenes.
# =============================================================================

# Import the DSL macros so we can use bare keywords
import IoTDSL

# ── The DSL Program ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This reads almost like natural language, yet it builds a fully typed
# metamodel instance (IoTSystem struct with all nested components).

result = system "SmartRoom" do
  broker "192.168.1.100", port: 1883

  node :pi4, ip: "192.168.1.10"
  node :pi5, ip: "192.168.1.11"

  topic "temperature/high",    qos: :at_least_once
  topic "temperature/normal",  qos: :at_least_once
  topic "distance/close",      qos: :at_most_once
  topic "alerts/warning",      qos: :at_least_once

  # ── Sensor: Temperature ──────────────────────────────────────────────
  sensor :temp_sensor, type: :temperature, gpio_pin: 4,
         sample_rate: {5, :seconds}, deployed_on: :pi4 do

    trigger :high_temp do
      condition :value, :greater_than, 30
      publish "temperature/high"
    end

    trigger :normal_temp do
      condition :value, :less_than, 20
      publish "temperature/normal"
    end
  end

  # ── Sensor: Distance ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  sensor :distance_sensor, type: :distance, gpio_pin: 27,
         sample_rate: {2, :seconds}, deployed_on: :pi4 do

    trigger :too_close do
      condition :value, :less_than, 20
      publish "distance/close"
    end
  end

  # ── Actuator: Cooling Fan ────────────────────────────────────────────
  actuator :cooling_fan, type: :relay, gpio_pin: 24, deployed_on: :pi5 do
    on_message "temperature/high",   turn: :on
    on_message "temperature/normal", turn: :off
  end

  # ── Actuator: Buzzer ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  actuator :buzzer, type: :buzzer, gpio_pin: 23, deployed_on: :pi5 do
    on_message "alerts/warning", turn: :on, for: {3, :seconds}
  end

  # ── Coordinator: Safety Logic ────────────────────────────────────────
  coordinator :room_safety, deployed_on: :pi5,
              subscribes_to: ["temperature/high", "distance/close"] do

    rule :heat_and_close do
      compound_condition :and, ["temperature/high", "distance/close"]
      publish "alerts/warning", message: "High temp + object nearby"
    end
  end
end

# ── Execute: Print the metamodel instance ──────────────────────────────────
IoTDSL.Printer.print(result)
```
